# Rule 100 - Frontend

## Baseline

- Responsive breakpoints: 375, 768, 1024, 1440.
- No emoji as UI icons. Use an icon library or inline SVG.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` and `prefers-color-scheme`.
- Keyboard + screen-reader reachable for every interactive element.

## Structure

- One component per file. Public export matches filename.
- Co-locate the component, its test, and its styles.
- Shared primitives live in `src/shared/ui/`.

## Styling

- Prefer __FRONTEND__ conventions already in the project.
- No inline hex colors in components. Use design tokens or CSS variables.

## State

- Local UI state in component.
- Server state via a single data-fetching library (no mixed patterns).
- Never store tokens / secrets in `localStorage` unless encrypted and justified in an ADR.

## Performance

- Lazy-load routes, heavy charts, image-heavy sections.
- Measure before optimizing. No premature memoization.

